t out of sync and needs to be corrected, plus I should verify the correct flag index for the ingress controller configuration. Writing JSON patch commands... I need to reconsider whether `data: null` actually clears the field or if I should use a JSON patch instead to be more precise. And thinking about the Ingress annotations—those are really the ingress-nginx configuration mechanism, so they count as non-default settings that should be reverted along with the controller config. I'll include them in the rollback and document the reasoning in the script.\n\nNow I'm ready to write out the final rollback script and handle the ConfigMap changes, though I should note that the `reload-trigger` annotation is just a mechanism to force reloads rather than actual configuration, so I'll leave that out of scope.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6054,"cache_read_input_tokens":35568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6054},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56157959-d438-486a-96f3-85adef401968","uuid":"eb615276-cc2f-425b-bfef-b9959896d127","request_id":"req_011CcMUMoyEgnTzRL4H7DVgg"}
