{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018U1NiEqvdtn7D2boohbAFz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01B3k5uEK4UTqGCED9y94cKr","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/rollback.sh","content":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# rollback.sh — Revert ingress-nginx non-default configuration to vanilla defaults.\n#\n# CAUTION: This script undoes live cluster configuration.\n# Review all steps carefully before executing.\n#\n# Non-default settings identified (cluster state: 2026-06-24):\n#\n#   1. ConfigMap ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller:\n#        OTel settings added to a ConfigMap that was created with data: null.\n#        Keys: enable-opentelemetry, log-format-upstream (with OTel trace/span\n#        fields appended), opentelemetry-collector-host, opentelemetry-collector-port,\n#        otel-sampler, otel-sampler-parent-based, otel-sampler-ratio.\n#\n#   2. Deployment ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller — args:\n#        --watch-ingress-without-class=false appended at position 10.\n#        This overrides the earlier --watch-ingress-without-class=true (position 8)\n#        and disables cross-class ingress watching.\n#\n#   3. Deployment ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller — env:\n#        OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://otel-collector.otel.svc:4317\n#        injected at env index 3 alongside the OTel ConfigMap settings.\n#\n#   4. Ingress demo/rate-api:\n#        nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-rps: \"1\"\n#        nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-burst-multiplier: \"1\"\n#        (added after initial deployment — last-applied-configuration shows annotations: {})\n#\n#   5. Ingress demo/demo-app:\n#        nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/rewrite-target: /\n#\n#   6. Ingress demo/canary-canary:\n#        nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary: \"true\"\n#        nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header: X-Canary\n#        nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header-value: always\n#\n#   7. Ingress demo/canary-alt:\n#        nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary: \"true\"\n#        nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header: X-Canary\n#        nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header-value: beta\n\nset -euo pipefail\n\necho \"=== Rollback: ingress-nginx non-default settings to vanilla defaults ===\"\necho \"\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Step 1 of 7: Reset the ingress-nginx-controller ConfigMap.\n#\n# The ConfigMap was created with data: null (vanilla default for ingress-nginx).\n# Every key currently present is a non-default addition for OpenTelemetry.\n# JSON patch is used so the operation fails explicitly if any key is missing\n# (rather than silently succeeding with stale state).\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\necho \"[1/7] Removing OTel keys from ingress-nginx-controller ConfigMap...\"\nkubectl -n ingress-nginx patch configmap ingress-nginx-controller \\\n  --type=json -p '[\n    {\"op\": \"remove\", \"path\": \"/data/enable-opentelemetry\"},\n    {\"op\": \"remove\", \"path\": \"/data/log-format-upstream\"},\n    {\"op\": \"remove\", \"path\": \"/data/opentelemetry-collector-host\"},\n    {\"op\": \"remove\", \"path\": \"/data/opentelemetry-collector-port\"},\n    {\"op\": \"remove\", \"path\": \"/data/otel-sampler\"},\n    {\"op\": \"remove\", \"path\": \"/data/otel-sampler-parent-based\"},\n    {\"op\": \"remove\", \"path\": \"/data/otel-sampler-ratio\"}\n  ]'\necho \"    Done.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Step 2 of 7: Remove the extra --watch-ingress-without-class=false arg.\n#\n# The original deployment (from last-applied-configuration) ends at\n# --publish-status-address=localhost (index 9). The flag at index 10\n# (--watch-ingress-without-class=false) was appended afterwards and silently\n# overrides the --watch-ingress-without-class=true at index 8.\n#\n# The \"test\" op gu